  "text": "Found references to the deprecated Envoy v2 API namespace envoy.api.v2 across both sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2 and sg-evals/data-plane-api--84e84367. In Envoy v1.31.2, the full api/envoy/api/v2/ directory tree is retained as FROZEN proto definitions (package_version_status = FROZEN) for backward compatibility. Key v2 proto files include cds.proto (ClusterDiscoveryService), lds.proto (ListenerDiscoveryService), rds.proto (RouteDiscoveryService), eds.proto (EndpointDiscoveryService), and discovery.proto (DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse). The data-plane-api repo has identical v2 protos under envoy/api/v2/. Active C++ source code references include: type_to_endpoint.cc (comments referencing v2 service names), listener_manager_impl.cc (references envoy.api.v2.core.Pipe), api/test/build/build_test.cc (v2 service method names), test/test_common/utility_test.cc (v2 type URLs), test_runtime.h (TestDeprecatedV2Api runtime flag). Python tooling: typedb_gen.py (v2 package list), constants.py (ENVOY_API_NAMESPACE_PREFIX = '.envoy.api.v2.'). Config examples: configs/using_deprecated_config.yaml. Header files: envoy/config/grpc_mux.h (doc comments with v2 type URLs). Fuzz corpus and v2alpha protos also contain v2 references but are not primary migration targets.",
